cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of selective strategies for mitigating TDoS attacks, which are a type of network security threat. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also focuses on telephony services and Voice over IP (VoIP), which suggests that cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another likely sub-category. The use of formal verification and modeling is also a key aspect of the paper, which could place it in cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the design and implementation of defenses, which could also place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
